      "title": "U.S. Crude Inventories Post Another Major Draw",
      "summary": "Crude oil inventories in the United States decreased by 6.1 million barrels during the week ending June 19, according to new data from the U.S. Energy Information Administration (EIA) released on Wednesday. The decrease brings commercial stockpiles to 412.1 million barrels, according to government data, which is now 7% below the five-year average for this time of year. The EIA\u2019s data release follows API\u2019s figures that were released a day earlier, which reported that crude oil inventories saw a draw of 765,000 barrels in the period.\u2026",
